Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1765/92 of 30 June 1992 establishing a support system of producers of certain arable crops (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1552/93 (2) and in particular Articles 12 and 16 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1113/93 of 6 May 1993 setting specific rules on compensatory payments on certain irrigated arable corps (3) provides that compensatory payment at the yield level set for irrigated arable crops is to be given within  a limit set for each production region; whereas these limits should be fixed taking account of the information forwarded by the Member States;
Whereas the information forwarded by Greece covers only areas irrigated during the reference period 1989 to 1991;
Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1765/92 provides that compensatory payments must be made by 31 December following the harvest at the latest;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Joint Management Committee for Cereals, Oils and Fats and Dried Fodder,
